Hi WP Perk,

We're writing today to let you know that we will be removing PHP 7.2 in the coming months. As you may know, PHP versions only receive support and security updates for a limited time, and that period is officially ending for PHP 7.2 this coming fall.

On October 1, 2020, we will disable the ability to switch to PHP 7.2 in live environments in MyKinsta. Sites running PHP 7.2 will be automatically upgraded to PHP 7.3 beginning October 29, 2020.

These sites will be automatically upgraded to PHP 7.3 beginning October 29, 2020. We recommend that you begin testing your sites now to avoid any potential issues.

Why is it important to use the latest PHP version?

The two main reasons are security and speed. Just as you upgrade WordPress itself to make sure you are protected against security vulnerabilities, you should do the same with PHP. In addition, upgrading PHP produces a significant speed increase. Check out our article on What's New in PHP 7.4.

How to upgrade to the latest version of PHP?

MyKinsta makes upgrading PHP versions as easy as selecting a new version from a dropdown list.

Please note that switching versions could break your site. You can utilize our staging environments to test the switch in a safe sandbox that will not affect your live site at all.

What if my site breaks?

Issues caused by upgrading PHP happen when code running on your site uses old functions that are no longer supported by newer versions of PHP. The culprit is likely to be a plugin or the active theme. Our safe PHP upgrades guide contains step-by-step instructions on how to troubleshoot this.

We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause you. We are dedicated to running the fastest and most secure environment on the market and that means that we need to make sure all sites are using technologies that are actively receiving security updates.
The Kinsta Team
